    <abstract id="aspace_e456fc8438efd361ad68905c6b2202c3"><title render="italic">Steel/City</title> was a University of Pittsburgh documentary theater production written for the Bicentennial in 1976, portraying the social and industrial history of Pittsburgh. This collection contains records from the development and production of the play and the audio cassettes of the post-play discussions and town meetings.</abstract>
